                      <h2>Big win over rivals!</h2>
                      <p>Our Junior B side had a massive win away from home on Sunday morning when they beat the champions from the last two years, Newmarket, in their own back yard. Apart from the last 15 minutes, when Newmarket were throwing everything at us, Avenue were the better side in this one. Avenue opened the scoring in the 15th minute when good paly down the left saw the ball squared to Mossy Hehir, who's right foot drive was too hot for the Newmarket keeper to handle. At this point, Avenue were on top and had most of possession. We doubled our advantage 10 minutes later when the Newmarket could only parry a shot and Mossey was on hand again to finish the job. With Pa Wilson and Kieran Thynne working well in the middle, were struggling to get into the game. They upped the efforts in the second half but it wasn't until Avenue started to tire that Newmarket started to control things. Although they did create some really good chances, they failed to find the Avenue net and the Avenue men left Newmarket with all three points!</p>
