                        <h2>Mixed Results in F.A.I cups</h2>
                        <p>Both of our sides in SFAI Cup action last Saturday exited their respective competitions; the U16 side went out to a strong Fairview Rangers side in Limerick while the U14 side were forced to concede home advantage to Lough Derg after Roslevan failed an early morning pitch inspection. This proved to be decisive as the side bowed out on a 1-0 scoreline to the North Tipp side. The season is now over for both these sides and they now get some well earned time off over the winter.
                           The Junior A side advanced to the open draw stages of the FAI Junior Cup after overcoming the Desmond League Champions Rathkeale on a 2-1 scoreline at Frank Healy Park on sunday last. The side trailed 1-0 at the interval but Mark Roche equalised early in the second half with Ronan Kerin grabbing the winner with 15 minutes left on the clock. The team and management are now anxiously awaiting the draw for the 5th round.</p>
